WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Welcome to the Elixir tutorial series.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.000
— Elixir runs on the BEAM virtual machine.
— It was designed for scalability.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.000
Always wear a helmet when riding a bicycle.
Safety is important for everyone.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.000
The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.
This sentence contains every letter of the alphabet.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Elixir is a functional programming language.
It runs on the Erlang virtual machine.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.000
Pattern matching is one of Elixir's most powerful features.
It allows you to destructure data with ease.
